   1import cadquery as cq

   4class SynthPrinter:
   5    """Each SynthPrinter object corresponds to a panel. You must add one, and
   6    only one panel, before performing operations on it.
   7
   8    Once you're done placing elements, you must call `render()` before
   9    exporting your work, to post-process things correctly.
  10    Elements will be aligned and oriented wrong if you skip this call.
  11
  12    The naming convention of methods is as follows:
  13
  14    - `addX()`: calls methods such as `cutX()`, `previewX()`, etc, operating on multiple
  15    layers. Skips drawing to disabled layers for performance, so disable unnecessary
  16    layers in the constructor while making your layout.
  17    In most cases, you want to call those methods instead of making the individual calls
  18    bundled in the `addX()` methods.
  19    - `cutX()`: makes a hole for X on the **panel** layer
  20    - `markX()`: draws marks for X on the **drillTemplate** layer.
  21    *Exporting a drill template is a WIP, it still takes a bit of tinkering to
  22    make the PDF the proper size.*
  23    - `previewX()`: draws boxes and cylinders to preview the size of footprints
  24    on the **preview** layer
  25    - `embossX()`: creates an element on the **emboss** layer. You can only 3D print
  26    quality embossings if you orient your panel with the back as the first layer.
  27    *Not implemented yet*
  28    - `engraveX()`: carves an engraving that does not cut all the way through the
  29    **panel** layer
  30    - `supportX()`: creates an element on the **supports** layer, used to strenghten
  31    panels and hold in place PCBs. You can only 3D print supports if you orient
  32    your panel with the front as the first layer.
  33
  34    Be sure to take a look at the bundled examples!
  35    """

 231    """
 232    You can override any of the defaultConfig settings by passing them as a
 233    parameter to the constructor. Look at the code for the full list of
 234    settings. Some are dynamically calculated from other settings, 
 235    in particular, the tolerances of most elements are expressed as a
 236    multiplier of the main tolerance value.
 237
 238    For example, to replace the main tolerance value of 0.4mm, create a
 239    new object as follows:
 240
 241        sp = SynthPrinter(
 242            tolerance=0.6,
 243        )
 244
 245    defaultConfig values are mostly dimensions that have been tested to
 246    work well with 3D printing. You are encouraged to try out the defaults 
 247    first. But with a different process than FDM 3D printing, you will want to
 248    make your own configuration profile."""
 249
 250    def __init__(self, **kwargs):
 251        self.config = self.defaultConfig.copy()
 252
 253        # override defaults
 254        for key, value in kwargs.items():
 255            if key in self.config:
 256                self.config[key] = value
 257
 258        # call lambdas
 259        for key, value in self.config.items():
 260            if callable(value):
 261                self.config[key] = value(self.config)
 262
 263        # Create layers
 264        self.panel = cq.Workplane("XY")
 265        self.preview = cq.Workplane("XY")
 266        self.emboss = cq.Workplane("XY")
 267        self.supports = cq.Workplane("XY")
 268        self.drillTemplate = cq.Workplane("XY")
 269
 270        self.panelAdded = False  # We can only have one or horrible things happen
 271

 282    def render(self, show_object=False):
 283        """You must call this before displaying or exporting your panel
 284        to post-process it properly.
 285
 286        If you give it the show_object function from Cq Editor as an
 287        argument, it will also display the object. When using Synth Printer
 288        from a different environment, just call without any argument.
 289        """
 290        # Shave off the sides of the panel if needed
 291        self.cutPanelWidthTolerance()
 292        # Move the supports where they belong
 293        self.supports = self.supports.translate(
 294            (0, 0, self.config["panelThickness"] / 2)
 295        )
 296        # Move the drill template above the panel
 297        self.drillTemplate = self.drillTemplate.translate(
 298            (0, 0, self.config["DrillTemplateDistance"])
 299        )
 300        # Rotate the layers for viewing
 301        self.panel = self.panel.rotate((0, 0, 0), (1, 0, 0), 180)
 302        self.preview = self.preview.rotate((0, 0, 0), (1, 0, 0), 180)
 303        self.emboss = self.emboss.rotate((0, 0, 0), (1, 0, 0), 180)
 304        self.supports = self.supports.rotate((0, 0, 0), (1, 0, 0), 180)
 305        self.drillTemplate = self.drillTemplate.rotate((0, 0, 0), (1, 0, 0), 180)
 306        # Display the layers if we're in CQ Editor
 307        if show_object and self.config["panelRender"]:
 308            show_object(
 309                self.panel,
 310                name="panel",
 311                options=self.config["panelShowOptions"],
 312            )
 313        if show_object and self.config["supportsRender"]:
 314            show_object(
 315                self.supports,
 316                name="supports",
 317                options=self.config["supportsShowOptions"],
 318            )
 319        if show_object and self.config["embossRender"]:
 320            show_object(
 321                self.emboss,
 322                name="emboss",
 323                options=self.config["embossShowOptions"],
 324            )
 325        if show_object and self.config["previewRender"]:
 326            show_object(
 327                self.preview,
 328                name="preview",
 329                options=self.config["previewShowOptions"],
 330            )
 331        if show_object and self.config["drillTemplateRender"]:
 332            show_object(
 333                self.drillTemplate,
 334                name="drillTemplate",
 335                options=self.config["drillTemplateShowOptions"],
 336            )

 338    def exportDrillTemplate(self, filename: str = "DrillTemplate.svg"):
 339        """Exports the drill template as a SVG file.
 340
 341        Before you print it, crop and scale it up or down in image editing
 342        software to match the size of one side!
 343
 344        TODO: Make it the perfect size out of the box.
 345
 346        You must activate the layer in the constructor first! Otherwise,
 347        drill marks are not rendered, for performance."""
 348        cq.exporters.export(
 349            self.drillTemplate,
 350            filename,
 351            opt={
 352                "width": 2000,
 353                "height": 2000,
 354                "marginLeft": 0,
 355                "marginTop": 0,
 356                "showAxes": False,
 357                "projectionDir": (0.0, 0.0, 1.0),
 358                "strokeWidth": 0.25,
 359                "strokeColor": (255, 0, 0),
 360                "hiddenColor": (0, 0, 255),
 361                "showHidden": False,
 362            },
 363        )

 375    def cutHole(self, x: float, y: float, diameter: float, depth: float = None):
 376        """Makes a circular hole, default depth is through the entire panel
 377
 378        x, y define the center."""
 379        self.panel = (
 380            self.panel.faces(">Z")
 381            .vertices("<XY")
 382            .workplane(centerOption="CenterOfMass")
 383            .center(x, y)
 384            .hole(diameter, depth)
 385        )
 386
 387    def cutRect(
 388        self,
 389        x: float,
 390        y: float,
 391        width: float,
 392        height: float,
 393        depth: float = 0,
 394        centered: bool = True,
 395    ):
 396        """Cuts a rectangular shape through the panel.
 397
 398        x, y define the center
 399
 400        `depth = 0` cuts through all.
 401        """
 402
 403        if depth == 0:
 404            depth = self.config["panelThickness"]
 405
 406        cutout = cq.Workplane("XY").box(width, height, depth)
 407
 408        if centered:
 409            cutout = cutout.translate(
 410                (
 411                    -self.config["panelWidth"] / 2 + x,
 412                    -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2 + y,
 413                    0,
 414                )
 415            )
 416        else:
 417            cutout = cutout.translate(
 418                (
 419                    -self.config["panelWidth"] / 2 + x + width / 2,
 420                    -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2 + y + height / 2,
 421                    0,
 422                )
 423            )
 424
 425        self.panel = (
 426            self.panel.faces(">Z")
 427            .vertices("<XY")
 428            .workplane(centerOption="CenterOfMass")
 429            .cut(cutout)
 430        )

 433    def previewCylinderOnBack(self, x: float, y: float, diameter: float, depth: float):
 434        """Adds a cylinder for preview on the back of the panel.
 435        It will be deeper by half the panel thickness.
 436
 437        x, y define the center."""
 438        self.preview = (
 439            self.preview.moveTo(
 440                -self.config["panelWidth"] / 2 + x,
 441                -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2 + y,
 442            )
 443            .circle(diameter / 2)
 444            .extrude(depth + self.config["panelThickness"] / 2)
 445        )
 446
 447    def previewCylinderOnFront(self, x: float, y: float, diameter: float, depth: float):
 448        """Adds a cylinder for preview on the front of the panel.
 449        It will be deeper by half the panel thickness.
 450
 451        x, y define the center."""
 452        self.preview = (
 453            self.preview.moveTo(
 454                -self.config["panelWidth"] / 2 + x,
 455                -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2 + y,
 456            )
 457            .circle(diameter / 2)
 458            .extrude(-depth - self.config["panelThickness"] / 2)
 459        )

 498    def addPanel(
 499        self,
 500        width: float,
 501        height: float,
 502        screwSlots: str = "auto",
 503    ):
 504        """Adds a rectangular panel of arbitrary dimensions.
 505        You can only add one.
 506
 507        Screw slots in the corners provide better tolerances than holes
 508        in a DIY printed system. If the panel is too small for four slots,
 509        there will be only two by default.
 510
 511
 512        TODO: Add Slots to the drill template
 513
 514
 515        screwSlots: options are "auto", "auto-tlbr", "auto-trbl", "auto-center", "none", "all", "tlbr", "trbl", "center"
 516        """
 517
 518        if self.panelAdded == True:
 519            raise Warning("Only one panel can be added")
 520        else:
 521            self.panelAdded = True
 522
 523        self.config["panelWidth"] = width
 524        self.config["panelHeight"] = height
 525
 526        # Make the main panel shape
 527        self.panel = self.panel.box(
 528            self.config["panelWidth"],
 529            self.config["panelHeight"],
 530            self.config["panelThickness"],
 531        )
 532
 533        # Initialize the drill template
 534        self.markOutline()
 535
 536        # Do we add screw slots?
 537        # default to "none" configuration
 538        screwSlotTopLeft = False
 539        screwSlotTopCenter = False
 540        screwSlotTopRight = False
 541        screwSlotBottomLeft = False
 542        screwSlotBottomCenter = False
 543        screwSlotBottomRight = False
 544        if (  # If too small for 4 slots
 545            self.config["m3screwSlotWidth"] * 2
 546            + (
 547                self.config["m3screwSlotDistanceFromSide"]
 548                - self.config["m3screwSlotWidth"] / 2
 549            )
 550            * 2
 551        ) > self.config["panelWidth"]:
 552            if screwSlots == "auto":
 553                screwSlots = "tlbr"
 554            if screwSlots == "auto-tlbr":
 555                screwSlots = "tlbr"
 556            if screwSlots == "auto-trbl":
 557                screwSlots = "trbl"
 558            if screwSlots == "auto-center":
 559                screwSlots = "center"
 560        else:  # Large enough for 4 slots
 561            if screwSlots == "auto":
 562                screwSlots = "all"
 563            if screwSlots == "auto-tlbr":
 564                screwSlots = "all"
 565            if screwSlots == "auto-trbl":
 566                screwSlots = "all"
 567            if screwSlots == "auto-center":
 568                screwSlots = "all"
 569        if screwSlots == "tlbr":
 570            screwSlotTopLeft = True
 571            screwSlotBottomRight = True
 572        if screwSlots == "trbl":
 573            screwSlotTopRight = True
 574            screwSlotBottomLeft = True
 575        if screwSlots == "center":
 576            screwSlotTopCenter = True
 577            screwSlotBottomCenter = True
 578        if screwSlots == "all":
 579            screwSlotTopLeft = True
 580            screwSlotTopRight = True
 581            screwSlotBottomLeft = True
 582            screwSlotBottomRight = True
 583
 584        screwPoints = []
 585        if screwSlotTopLeft:
 586            screwPoints.append(
 587                (
 588                    self.config["m3screwSlotDistanceFromSide"],
 589                    self.config["panelHeight"]
 590                    - self.config["m3screwSlotDistanceFromTop"],
 591                )
 592            )
 593        if screwSlotTopCenter:
 594            screwPoints.append(
 595                (
 596                    self.config["panelWidth"] / 2,
 597                    self.config["panelHeight"]
 598                    - self.config["m3screwSlotDistanceFromTop"],
 599                )
 600            )
 601        if screwSlotTopRight:
 602            screwPoints.append(
 603                (
 604                    self.config["panelWidth"]
 605                    - self.config["m3screwSlotDistanceFromSide"],
 606                    self.config["panelHeight"]
 607                    - self.config["m3screwSlotDistanceFromTop"],
 608                )
 609            )
 610        if screwSlotBottomLeft:
 611            screwPoints.append(
 612                (
 613                    self.config["m3screwSlotDistanceFromSide"],
 614                    self.config["m3screwSlotDistanceFromBottom"],
 615                )
 616            )
 617        if screwSlotBottomCenter:
 618            screwPoints.append(
 619                (
 620                    self.config["panelWidth"] / 2,
 621                    self.config["m3screwSlotDistanceFromBottom"],
 622                )
 623            )
 624        if screwSlotBottomRight:
 625            screwPoints.append(
 626                (
 627                    self.config["panelWidth"]
 628                    - self.config["m3screwSlotDistanceFromSide"],
 629                    self.config["m3screwSlotDistanceFromBottom"],
 630                )
 631            )
 632        if screwPoints != []:
 633            self.panel = (
 634                self.panel.faces(">Z")
 635                .workplane()
 636                .center(-self.config["panelWidth"] / 2, -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2)
 637                .pushPoints(screwPoints)
 638                .slot2D(
 639                    self.config["m3screwSlotWidth"],
 640                    self.config["m3screwSlotHeight"],
 641                    0,
 642                )
 643                .cutThruAll()
 644            )

 646    def addEurorackPanel(
 647        self,
 648        hp: int,
 649        screwSlots="auto",
 650    ):
 651        """Adds a Eurorack panel with screw slots. Eurorack width is defined in hp().
 652
 653        Eurorack sizes are generally an even number of hp, such as 4hp or 8hp.
 654        3hp and 5hp are the only odd number sizes commonly seen in commercial hardware.
 655
 656        Screw slots in the corners provide better tolerances than holes
 657        in a DIY printed system. If the panel is too small for four slots,
 658        there will be only two by default.
 659
 660        screwSlots: options are "auto", "auto-tlbr", "auto-trbl", "auto-center", "none", "all", "tlbr", "trbl", "center"
 661        """
 662        self.config["panelWidthTolerance"] = self.config["eurorackWidthTolerance"]
 663        self.addPanel(self.config["hp"] * hp, self.config["eurorackHeight"], screwSlots)
 664

 667        hp: int,
 668        screwSlots="auto",
 669    ):
 670        """Adds a 1U Tile (Intellijel size) panel with screw slots. Eurorack width is defined in hp().
 671
 672        Note that there are two incompatible 1U tile standards: Intellijel and PulpLogic.
 673
 674        Screw slots in the corners provide better tolerances than holes
 675        in a DIY printed system. If the panel is too small for four slots,
 676        there will be only two by default.
 677
 678        screwSlots: options are "auto", "auto-tlbr", "auto-trbl", "auto-center", "none", "all", "tlbr", "trbl", "center"
 679        """
 680        self.config["panelWidthTolerance"] = self.config["1UIJWidthTolerance"]
 681        self.addPanel(self.config["hp"] * hp, self.config["1UIJHeight"], screwSlots)

 683    def addKosmoPanel(
 684        self,
 685        khp: int,
 686        screwSlots="auto",
 687    ):
 688        """Adds a Kosmo panel with screw slots. khp argument is the amount of 25mm columns.
 689
 690        Kosmo, also known as Metric 5U, is a format compatible with Eurorack
 691        popularized by Youtuber Sam Battle (Look Mum No Computer), that uses big jacks.
 692        It has a horizontal pitch of 25mm (called khp in Synth Printer for simplicity)
 693
 694        Screw slots in the corners provide better tolerances than holes
 695        in a DIY printed system. Kosmo panels are always large enough for four slots,
 696        but you can explicitly set a different configuration of slots.
 697
 698        screwSlots: options are "auto", "auto-tlbr", "auto-trbl", "auto-center", "none", "all", "tlbr", "trbl", "center"
 699        """
 700        self.config["panelWidthTolerance"] = self.config["kosmoWidthTolerance"]
 701        self.addPanel(
 702            self.config["khp"] * khp,
 703            self.config["kosmoHeight"],
 704            screwSlots=screwSlots,
 705        )

 707    def cutPanelWidthTolerance(self):
 708        """Automatically called during `render()` for Eurorack and 1UIJ:
 709        makes the panel a bit smaller than its nominal size laterally to account
 710        for thermal expansion and misaligned neighboring panels.
 711        Kosmo panels are naturally a bit smaller than the hp grid (they are on a
 712        25mm grid, while hp are on a 5.08mm grid), as a result, they don't need
 713        this shave.
 714        """
 715        # FIXME: Trial and error values that make no sense.
 716        # Something's broken elsewhere!
 717        # FIXME: Test print Euro / IJ: Do the tolerances provide enough extrusions?
 718        if self.config["panelWidthTolerance"] == 0:
 719            return
 720        self.cutRect(
 721            0,
 722            0,
 723            self.config["panelWidthTolerance"],
 724            self.config["panelHeight"] * 2,
 725            False,
 726        )
 727
 728        self.cutRect(
 729            self.config["panelWidth"] - self.config["panelWidthTolerance"] / 2,
 730            0,
 731            self.config["panelWidthTolerance"],
 732            self.config["panelHeight"] * 2,
 733            False,
 734        )

 740    def engraveLine(
 741        self,
 742        fromX: float,
 743        fromY: float,
 744        angle: float,
 745        length: float,
 746        width: float,
 747        depth: float = 0,
 748    ):
 749        """Engraves a line on the front of the panel.
 750
 751        If the depth parameter is omitted or 0, the default depth is used.
 752
 753        Be sure to inspect both sides of the print to make sure there aren't
 754        any sections that are too thin!
 755        """
 756        if not self.config["panelRender"]:
 757            return
 758        if depth == 0:
 759            depth = self.config["panelEngravingDepth"]
 760        cutout = (
 761            cq.Workplane("XY")
 762            .lineTo(-width / 2, 0)
 763            .lineTo(-width / 2, -length)
 764            .lineTo(width / 2, -length)
 765            .lineTo(width / 2, 0)
 766            .close()
 767            .extrude(depth)
 768            .rotate((0, 0, 0), (0, 0, 1), angle)
 769            .translate(
 770                (
 771                    -self.config["panelWidth"] / 2 + fromX,
 772                    -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2 + fromY,
 773                    -self.config["panelThickness"] / 2,
 774                )
 775            )
 776        )
 777        self.panel = (
 778            self.panel.faces(">Z")
 779            .vertices("<XY")
 780            .workplane(centerOption="CenterOfMass")
 781            .cut(cutout)
 782        )

 793    def cutRail(
 794        self,
 795        x: float,
 796        y: float,
 797        hpWidth: int,
 798        centered: bool = True,
 799        orientation: str = "horizontal",
 800    ):
 801        """Make a hole for a hp rail. The rail is added to the supports layer,
 802        not the panel layer."""
 803        if not self.config["panelRender"]:
 804            return
 805        width = hp(hpWidth) + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2
 806        height = self.config["railsHeight"] + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2
 807        if orientation == "vertical":
 808            width, height = height, width
 809        if centered:
 810            self.cutRect(x, y, width, height, 0, centered)
 811        else:
 812            self.cutRect(
 813                x - self.config["cradleTolerance"],
 814                y - self.config["cradleTolerance"],
 815                width,
 816                height,
 817                0,
 818                centered,
 819            )
 820
 821    def supportRail(
 822        self,
 823        _x: float,
 824        _y: float,
 825        hpWidth: int,
 826        centered: bool = True,
 827        orientation: str = "horizontal",
 828    ):
 829        """Adds a hp rail to the support layer. Requires a hole from cutRail()."""
 830        if not self.config["supportsRender"]:
 831            return
 832        width = hp(hpWidth) + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2
 833        height = self.config["railsHeight"] + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2
 834        if orientation != "horizontal":
 835            width, height = height, width
 836
 837        if centered:
 838            x = -self.config["panelWidth"] / 2 + _x
 839            y = -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2 + _y
 840        else:
 841            x = (
 842                -self.config["panelWidth"] / 2
 843                + _x
 844                + width / 2
 845                - self.config["cradleTolerance"]
 846            )
 847            y = (
 848                -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2
 849                + _y
 850                + height / 2
 851                - self.config["cradleTolerance"]
 852            )
 853
 854        self.supports = (
 855            # Extrude on the inside
 856            self.supports.moveTo(x, y)
 857            .rect(width, height)
 858            .extrude(-self.config["panelThickness"] + self.config["railsFrontRecess"])
 859            # Extrude on the back
 860            .moveTo(x, y)
 861            .rect(width, height)
 862            .extrude(self.config["railsSupportDepthBack"])
 863        )
 864
 865        if orientation == "horizontal":
 866            x = (
 867                -self.config["panelWidth"] / 2
 868                + _x
 869                + (self.config["hp"] - self.config["railsScrewDiameter"]) / 2
 870                + self.config["railsScrewDiameter"] / 2
 871            )
 872            if centered:
 873                x = x - hp(hpWidth) / 2
 874        else:
 875            y = (
 876                -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2
 877                + _y
 878                + (self.config["hp"] - self.config["railsScrewDiameter"]) / 2
 879                + self.config["railsScrewDiameter"] / 2
 880            )
 881            if centered:
 882                y = y - hp(hpWidth) / 2
 883
 884        # Can't get rarray to work here.
 885        if orientation == "horizontal":
 886            for n in range(hpWidth):
 887                self.supports = (
 888                    self.supports.moveTo(x + n * self.config["hp"], y)
 889                    .circle(self.config["railsScrewDiameter"] / 2)
 890                    .cutThruAll()
 891                )
 892        else:
 893            for n in range(hpWidth):
 894                self.supports = (
 895                    self.supports.moveTo(x, y + n * self.config["hp"])
 896                    .circle(self.config["railsScrewDiameter"] / 2)
 897                    .cutThruAll()
 898                )

 900    def addRail(
 901        self,
 902        x: float,
 903        y: float,
 904        hpWidth: int,
 905        centered: bool = True,
 906        orientation: str = "horizontal",
 907    ):
 908        """Adds a recessed hp rail. The rail is added to the supports layer,
 909         not the panel layer. Good to build cradles: put a Eurorack modules on
 910        a Kosmo faceplate, or 1U on a Eurorack one.
 911
 912        x, y define the center.
 913
 914        orientation is "horizontal" by default, otherwise "vertical"
 915        """
 916        self.cutRail(x, y, hpWidth, centered, orientation)
 917        self.supportRail(x, y, hpWidth, centered, orientation)

 919    def previewPanel(
 920        self,
 921        x: float,
 922        y: float,
 923        hpWidth: int,
 924        height: float,
 925        centered: bool = True,
 926        orientation: str = "horizontal",
 927    ):
 928        if not self.config["previewRender"]:
 929            return
 930        if orientation == "horizontal":
 931            if centered:
 932                self.previewBoxOnFront(
 933                    x + self.config["cradleTolerance"],
 934                    y
 935                    + height / 2
 936                    - self.config["railsHeight"] / 2
 937                    + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2,
 938                    hp(hpWidth),
 939                    height,
 940                    1.6,
 941                )
 942            else:
 943                self.previewBoxOnFront(
 944                    x + hp(hpWidth) / 2 + self.config["cradleTolerance"],
 945                    y + height / 2 + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2,
 946                    hp(hpWidth),
 947                    height,
 948                    1.6,
 949                )
 950        else:  # vertical
 951            if centered:
 952                self.previewBoxOnFront(
 953                    x
 954                    + height / 2
 955                    - self.config["railsHeight"] / 2
 956                    + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2,
 957                    y + self.config["cradleTolerance"],
 958                    height,
 959                    hp(hpWidth),
 960                    1.6,
 961                )
 962            else:
 963                self.previewBoxOnFront(
 964                    x + height / 2 + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2,
 965                    y + hp(hpWidth) / 2 + self.config["cradleTolerance"],
 966                    height,
 967                    hp(hpWidth),
 968                    1.6,
 969                )

 971    def addCradle(
 972        self,
 973        x: float,
 974        y: float,
 975        hpWidth: int,
 976        height: float,
 977        centered: bool = True,
 978        orientation: str = "horizontal",
 979        supportTop: bool = True,
 980        supportRight: bool = True,
 981        supportBottom: bool = True,
 982        supportLeft: bool = True,
 983    ):
 984        """Adds a pair of recessed hp rails and a hole for modules.
 985        The rail is added to the supports layer, not the panel layer.
 986        You probably want to use `addEurorackCradle()` or
 987        `add1UIJCradle()` instead.
 988        """
 989        # Add the two rails
 990        self.addRail(x, y, hpWidth, centered, orientation)
 991        if orientation == "horizontal":
 992            self.addRail(
 993                x,
 994                y + height - self.config["m3Diameter"] * 2,
 995                hpWidth,
 996                centered,
 997                orientation,
 998            )
 999        else:
1000            self.addRail(
1001                x + height - self.config["m3Diameter"] * 2,
1002                y,
1003                hpWidth,
1004                centered,
1005                orientation,
1006            )
1007        # Cut a hole between those rails
1008        if orientation == "horizontal":
1009            if centered:
1010                self.cutRect(
1011                    x,
1012                    y + height / 2 - self.config["railsHeight"] / 2,
1013                    hp(hpWidth) + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2,
1014                    height + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2,
1015                    0,
1016                    centered,
1017                )
1018                offset = -hp(hpWidth) / 2
1019                x1 = x - 3 + offset
1020                x2 = x + hp(hpWidth) + offset
1021                y1 = y - self.config["railsHeight"] / 2 - 3
1022                y2 = y + height - 2
1023            else:
1024                self.cutRect(
1025                    x - self.config["cradleTolerance"],
1026                    y - self.config["cradleTolerance"],
1027                    hp(hpWidth) + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2,
1028                    height + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2,
1029                    0,
1030                    centered,
1031                )
1032                offset = 0
1033                x1 = x - 3 + offset
1034                x2 = x + hp(hpWidth) + offset
1035                y1 = y - 3
1036                y2 = y + height + 2
1037            w = hp(hpWidth) + 6
1038            h = height + 6
1039        else:  # vertical
1040            if centered:
1041                self.cutRect(
1042                    x + height / 2 - self.config["railsHeight"] / 2,
1043                    y,
1044                    height + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2,
1045                    hp(hpWidth) + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2,
1046                    0,
1047                    centered,
1048                )
1049                x1 = (
1050                    x - self.config["railsHeight"] * 0.7
1051                )  # FIXME: IDK why it needs this number. This prolly breaks alt values.
1052                x2 = x + height - 2
1053                y1 = y - hp(hpWidth) / 2 - 3
1054                y2 = y + hp(hpWidth) / 2
1055            else:
1056                self.cutRect(
1057                    x - self.config["cradleTolerance"],
1058                    y - self.config["cradleTolerance"],
1059                    height + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2,
1060                    hp(hpWidth) + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2,
1061                    0,
1062                    centered,
1063                )
1064                x1 = x - 3
1065                x2 = x + height + 2
1066                y1 = y - 3
1067                y2 = y + hp(hpWidth)
1068            w = height + 6
1069            h = hp(hpWidth) + 6
1070        if supportTop:
1071            self.supportBar(
1072                x1,
1073                y1,
1074                w,
1075                3 + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2,
1076                self.config["railsSupportDepthBack"],
1077                False,
1078            )
1079        if supportBottom:
1080            self.supportBar(
1081                x1,
1082                y2 - self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2,
1083                w,
1084                3 + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2,
1085                self.config["railsSupportDepthBack"],
1086                False,
1087            )
1088        if supportLeft:
1089            self.supportBar(
1090                x1,
1091                y1,
1092                3 + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2,
1093                h,
1094                self.config["railsSupportDepthBack"],
1095                False,
1096            )
1097        if supportRight:
1098            self.supportBar(
1099                x2 - self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2,
1100                y1,
1101                3 + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2,
1102                h,
1103                self.config["railsSupportDepthBack"],
1104                False,
1105            )
1106
1107        self.previewPanel(x, y, hpWidth, height, centered, orientation)
1108
1109    def addEurorackCradle(
1110        self,
1111        x: float,
1112        y: float,
1113        hpWidth: int,
1114        centered: bool = True,
1115        orientation: str = "horizontal",
1116        supportTop: bool = True,
1117        supportRight: bool = True,
1118        supportBottom: bool = True,
1119        supportLeft: bool = True,
1120    ):
1121        """Adds a pair of recessed hp rails and a hole for modules.
1122        The rail is added to the supports layer, not the panel layer.
1123        Screw holes are spaced vertically 122.5mm apart for Eurorack.
1124        There are supports around the cradle for increased strength.
1125
1126        This footprint will probbly not work with custom values
1127        without modifying the code.
1128
1129        Printed rails hold modules satisfactorily using M3x8mm screws, and
1130        the holes last a dozen screwing cycles before becoming too enlarged
1131        to hold things well. For increased safety, use longer screws and nuts.
1132
1133        Strongly advised to print with supports, but will still print OK without.
1134
1135        x, y define the center hole of the top rail if centered, that is,
1136        if the rail is 3hp, the coordinates define the center of the 2nd hole.
1137        If not centered, the coordinates define the top-left of the
1138        opening window.
1139
1140        orientation is "horizontal" by default, otherwise "vertical"
1141
1142        supportTop, supportRight, supportBottom, supportLeft can be set to False
1143        to allow stacking rails next to each other."""
1144        self.addCradle(
1145            x,
1146            y,
1147            hpWidth,
1148            self.config["eurorackHeight"],
1149            centered,
1150            orientation,
1151            supportTop,
1152            supportRight,
1153            supportBottom,
1154            supportLeft,
1155        )

1267            .moveTo(  # Bottom
1268                0,

1270                - self.config["DrillTemplateMarkThickness"] / 2,

1273                self.config["panelWidth"],
1274                self.config["DrillTemplateMarkThickness"],
1275            )
1276            .extrude(self.config["DrillTemplateMarkThickness"])
1277            .moveTo(  # Left
1278                -self.config["panelWidth"] / 2
1279                + self.config["DrillTemplateMarkThickness"] / 2,
1280                0,
1281            )
1282            .rect(
1283                self.config["DrillTemplateMarkThickness"],
1284                self.config["panelHeight"],
1285            )
1286            .extrude(self.config["DrillTemplateMarkThickness"])
1287            .moveTo(  # Right
1288                self.config["panelWidth"] / 2
1289                - self.config["DrillTemplateMarkThickness"] / 2,
1290                0,
1291            )
1292            .rect(
1293                self.config["DrillTemplateMarkThickness"],
1294                self.config["panelHeight"],
1295            )
1296            .extrude(self.config["DrillTemplateMarkThickness"])
1297        )
1298
1299    def markCross(self, x: float, y: float):
1300        """Adds a mark on the drill template layer. At typical synth panel
1301        sizes, it will show up as a cross the perfect size for printing out and
1302        using as a drill template.
1303
1304        x, y define the center of the mark as seen from the front.
1305        """
1306        self.drillTemplate = (
1307            self.drillTemplate.moveTo(
1308                -self.config["panelWidth"] / 2 + x,
1309                -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2 + y,
1310            )
1311            .rect(
1312                self.config["DrillTemplateMarkLength"],
1313                self.config["DrillTemplateMarkThickness"],
1314            )
1315            .extrude(self.config["DrillTemplateMarkThickness"])
1316            .moveTo(
1317                -self.config["panelWidth"] / 2 + x,
1318                -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2 + y,
1319            )
1320            .rect(
1321                self.config["DrillTemplateMarkThickness"],
1322                self.config["DrillTemplateMarkLength"],
1323            )
1324            .extrude(self.config["DrillTemplateMarkThickness"])
1325        )
1326
1327    def markRect(self, x: float, y: float, width: float, height: float):
1328        """Marks a rectangle on the drill template.
1329
1330        x, y define the center."""
1331
1332        self.drillTemplate = (
1333            self.drillTemplate.moveTo(
1334                -self.config["panelWidth"] / 2 + x,
1335                -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2 + y,
1336            )
1337            .rect(width, height)
1338            .extrude(1)
1339            .moveTo(
1340                -self.config["panelWidth"] / 2 + x,
1341                -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2 + y,
1342            )
1343            .rect(
1344                width - self.config["DrillTemplateMarkThickness"] * 2,
1345                height - self.config["DrillTemplateMarkThickness"] * 2,
1346            )
1347            .cutThruAll()
1348        )
1349
1350    def markHole(self, x: float, y: float, diameter: float):
1351        """Marks a circular hole on the drill template.
1352
1353        x, y define the center.
1354
1355        FIXME: Nasty implementation, and requires marking circles before crosses
1356
1357        """
1358        self.drillTemplate = (
1359            self.drillTemplate.moveTo(
1360                -self.config["panelWidth"] / 2 + x,
1361                -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2 + y,
1362            )
1363            .circle(diameter / 2)
1364            .extrude(1)
1365            .moveTo(
1366                -self.config["panelWidth"] / 2 + x,
1367                -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2 + y,
1368            )
1369            .circle(diameter / 2 - self.config["DrillTemplateMarkThickness"])
1370            .cutThruAll()
1371        )
1372        return

1551    #######################################################################
1552    ### Potentiometers, rotary encoders, sliders
1553    #######################################################################
1554
1555    def cutPotentiometer(
1556        self,
1557        x: float,
1558        y: float,
1559        notchOrientation: str = "all",
1560        rotaryEncoderNotch: bool = False,
1561    ):
1562        if not self.config["panelRender"]:
1563            return
1564        self.cutHole(x, y, self.config["potentiometerHoleDiameterWithTolerance"])
1565        # List the notches
1566        points = []  # default to "none" configuration
1567        if notchOrientation == "top" or notchOrientation == "all":
1568            points.append((0, -self.config["potentiometerNotchDistanceFromCenter"]))
1569        if notchOrientation == "right" or notchOrientation == "all":
1570            points.append((self.config["potentiometerNotchDistanceFromCenter"], 0))
1571        if notchOrientation == "bottom" or notchOrientation == "all":
1572            points.append((0, self.config["potentiometerNotchDistanceFromCenter"]))
1573        if notchOrientation == "left" or notchOrientation == "all":
1574            points.append((-self.config["potentiometerNotchDistanceFromCenter"], 0))
1575        # Cut the notches
1576        self.panel = (
1577            self.panel.faces(">Z")
1578            .vertices("<XY")
1579            .workplane(centerOption="CenterOfMass")
1580            .center(x, y)
1581            .pushPoints(points)
1582            .hole(
1583                self.config["potentiometerNotchDiameter"],
1584                self.config["potentiometerNotchDepth"],
1585            )
1586        )
1587        # Notch for the encoder
1588        if rotaryEncoderNotch:
1589            self.panel = (
1590                self.panel.faces(">Z")
1591                .vertices("<XY")
1592                .workplane(centerOption="CenterOfMass")
1593                .center(x, y)
1594                .rect(
1595                    self.config["rotaryEncoderWidthWithTolerance"],
1596                    self.config["rotaryEncoderHeightWithTolerance"],
1597                )
1598                .cutBlind(-self.config["rotaryEncoderNotchDepth"])
1599            )
1600
1601    def previewPotentiometer(self, x: float, y: float, lugsOrientation: str = "all"):
1602        if not self.config["previewRender"]:
1603            return
1604        self.previewCylinderOnFront(x, y, 6, 21)
1605        self.previewCylinderOnFront(x, y, 9.6, 1.6)
1606        self.previewCylinderOnBack(x, y, 16, 8)
1607        if lugsOrientation == "all" or lugsOrientation == "bottom":
1608            self.previewBoxOnBack(x, y + 8, 15, 18, 2.4)
1609        if lugsOrientation == "top":
1610            self.previewBoxOnBack(x, y - 8, 15, 18, 2.4)
1611        if lugsOrientation == "left":
1612            self.previewBoxOnBack(x - 8, y, 18, 15, 2.4)
1613        if lugsOrientation == "right":
1614            self.previewBoxOnBack(x + 8, y, 18, 15, 2.4)

1616    def markPotentiometer(self, x: float, y: float):
1617        if not self.config["drillTemplateRender"]:
1618            return
1619        self.markHole(x, y, self.config["potentiometerHoleDiameterWithTolerance"])
1620        self.markCross(x, y)
1621
1622    def addPotentiometer(
1623        self,
1624        x: float,
1625        y: float,
1626        notchOrientation: str = "all",
1627        lugsOrientation: str = "all",
1628        rotaryEncoderNotch: bool = False,
1629    ):
1630        """Fits most types of panel-mount potentiometers with a 6mm shaft.
1631
1632        There will be four notches around the hole, allowing you to catch the
1633        retaining tab of the potentiometer in the most convenient orientation
1634        possible.
1635
1636        Common rotary encoders such as EC11 could use a thinner panel for the
1637        shaft to protrude sufficiently, in which case, set `rotaryEncoderNotch`
1638        to `True` to cut a rectangle in the back of the  panel.
1639
1640        If you want a knob, add it separately with addKnob()
1641
1642        The orientation parameters are seen from the front, and are:
1643        "all", "none", "top", "left", "right", "bottom".
1644
1645        The retaining notches aren't always on the same side, depending on the
1646        type of potentiometer! If in doubt, just leave it to "all" to add 4 notches.
1647
1648        The preview size for the lugs doesn't account for the possibility of bending them,
1649        so it might be safe to have this area overlap other stuff a little.
1650        """
1651        self.cutPotentiometer(x, y, notchOrientation, rotaryEncoderNotch)
1652        self.previewPotentiometer(x, y, lugsOrientation)
1653        self.markPotentiometer(x, y)
1654

1660    def addKnob(self, x: float, y: float, diameter: float, depth: float):

1662        potentiometers and rotary encoders!
1663
1664        Since there is a lot of variation in knob sizes, and sometimes the
1665        shaft is left exposed without a knob, it's not added automatically."""
1666        self.previewKnob(x, y, diameter, depth)

2013    def cutDisplayWindow(
2014        self,
2015        x: float,
2016        y: float,
2017        windowWidth: float = 30,
2018        windowHeight: float = 15,
2019        windowHorizontalOffset: float = 0,
2020        windowVerticalOffset: float = -5,
2021        screwsHorizontalDistance: float = 40,
2022        screwsVerticalDistance: float = 40,
2023        addScrews: bool = True,
2024    ):
2025        # FIXME: This is the nastiest way possible to implement a fillet
2026        # but the only one I could figure out.
2027
2028        cutout = (
2029            cq.Workplane("XY")
2030            .box(
2031                windowWidth + self.config["panelThickness"],
2032                windowHeight + self.config["panelThickness"],
2033                self.config["panelThickness"],
2034            )
2035            .edges(">Z")
2036            .fillet(self.config["panelThickness"] * 0.99)
2037            .translate(
2038                (
2039                    -self.config["panelWidth"] / 2 + x + windowHorizontalOffset,
2040                    -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2 + y + windowVerticalOffset,
2041                    0,
2042                )
2043            )
2044        )
2045        self.panel = (
2046            self.panel.faces(">Z")
2047            .vertices("<XY")
2048            .workplane(centerOption="CenterOfMass")
2049            .cut(cutout)
2050        )
2051
2052        # Next, the actual cutout
2053        self.panel = (
2054            self.panel.faces(">Z")
2055            .vertices("<XY")
2056            .workplane(centerOption="CenterOfMass")
2057            .center(x + windowHorizontalOffset, y + windowVerticalOffset)
2058            .rect(windowWidth, windowHeight)
2059            .cutThruAll()
2060        )
2061
2062        # Now, the screws
2063        if addScrews:
2064            self.panel = (
2065                self.panel.faces(">Z")
2066                .vertices("<XY")
2067                .workplane(centerOption="CenterOfMass")
2068                .center(x, y)
2069                .rect(
2070                    screwsHorizontalDistance,
2071                    screwsVerticalDistance,
2072                    forConstruction=True,
2073                )
2074                .vertices()
2075                .circle(self.config["m2DiameterWithTolerance"] / 2)
2076                .cutThruAll()
2077            )

2080        self,

2100            self.markHole(
2101                x - screwsHorizontalDistance / 2,
2102                y - screwsVerticalDistance / 2,
2103                self.config["m2DiameterWithTolerance"],
2104            )
2105            self.markHole(
2106                x + screwsHorizontalDistance / 2,
2107                y - screwsVerticalDistance / 2,
2108                self.config["m2DiameterWithTolerance"],
2109            )
2110            self.markHole(
2111                x - screwsHorizontalDistance / 2,
2112                y + screwsVerticalDistance / 2,
2113                self.config["m2DiameterWithTolerance"],
2114            )
2115            self.markHole(
2116                x + screwsHorizontalDistance / 2,
2117                y + screwsVerticalDistance / 2,
2118                self.config["m2DiameterWithTolerance"],
2119            )
2120            self.markCross(
2121                x - screwsHorizontalDistance / 2,
2122                y - screwsVerticalDistance / 2,
2123            )
2124            self.markCross(
2125                x + screwsHorizontalDistance / 2,
2126                y - screwsVerticalDistance / 2,
2127            )
2128            self.markCross(
2129                x - screwsHorizontalDistance / 2,
2130                y + screwsVerticalDistance / 2,
2131            )
2132            self.markCross(
2133                x + screwsHorizontalDistance / 2,
2134                y + screwsVerticalDistance / 2,
2135            )

2196def hp(hp: float):
2197    """Converts Eurorack Horizontal Pitch to millimeters (1hp = 0.2in = 5.08mm).
2198    Useful to align things to the grid."""
2199    return hp * 5.08
2200
2201
2202def khp(khp: float):
2203    """Converts khp (Kosmo HP) to millimeters (1khp = 25mm).
2204    Useful to align things to the the custom kcol / krow grid."""
2205    return khp * 25
2206
2207
2208def kcol(kcol: float):
2209    """Custom Kosmo grid system: each kcol is at the center of a 25mm section"""
2210    return (kcol - 1) * 25 + 12.5
2211
2212
2213def krow(krow: float):
2214    """Custom Kosmo grid system: each krow is 25mm, first starts 25mm from top"""
2215    return (krow) * 25
2216
2217
2218def hcol(hcol: float):
2219    """Custom Eurorack grid system: each hcol is at the center of a 1hp section"""
2220    return (hcol - 1) * hp(1) + hp(0.5)
2221
2222
2223def hrow(hrow: float):
2224    """Custom Eurorack grid system: each hrow is 1hp but vertically,
2225    first starts 1hp from top"""
2226    return (hrow) * hp(1)

2229# To generate API reference: ``pdoc synthprinter.py -o ./``
class SynthPrinter: 
   5class SynthPrinter:
   6    """Each SynthPrinter object corresponds to a panel. You must add one, and
   7    only one panel, before performing operations on it.
   8
   9    Once you're done placing elements, you must call `render()` before
  10    exporting your work, to post-process things correctly.
  11    Elements will be aligned and oriented wrong if you skip this call.
  12
  13    The naming convention of methods is as follows:
  14
  15    - `addX()`: calls methods such as `cutX()`, `previewX()`, etc, operating on multiple
  16    layers. Skips drawing to disabled layers for performance, so disable unnecessary
  17    layers in the constructor while making your layout.
  18    In most cases, you want to call those methods instead of making the individual calls
  19    bundled in the `addX()` methods.
  20    - `cutX()`: makes a hole for X on the **panel** layer
  21    - `markX()`: draws marks for X on the **drillTemplate** layer.
  22    *Exporting a drill template is a WIP, it still takes a bit of tinkering to
  23    make the PDF the proper size.*
  24    - `previewX()`: draws boxes and cylinders to preview the size of footprints
  25    on the **preview** layer
  26    - `embossX()`: creates an element on the **emboss** layer. You can only 3D print
  27    quality embossings if you orient your panel with the back as the first layer.
  28    *Not implemented yet*
  29    - `engraveX()`: carves an engraving that does not cut all the way through the
  30    **panel** layer
  31    - `supportX()`: creates an element on the **supports** layer, used to strenghten
  32    panels and hold in place PCBs. You can only 3D print supports if you orient
  33    your panel with the front as the first layer.
  34
  35    Be sure to take a look at the bundled examples!
  36    """

 232    """
 233    You can override any of the defaultConfig settings by passing them as a
 234    parameter to the constructor. Look at the code for the full list of
 235    settings. Some are dynamically calculated from other settings, 
 236    in particular, the tolerances of most elements are expressed as a
 237    multiplier of the main tolerance value.
 238
 239    For example, to replace the main tolerance value of 0.4mm, create a
 240    new object as follows:
 241
 242        sp = SynthPrinter(
 243            tolerance=0.6,
 244        )
 245
 246    defaultConfig values are mostly dimensions that have been tested to
 247    work well with 3D printing. You are encouraged to try out the defaults 
 248    first. But with a different process than FDM 3D printing, you will want to
 249    make your own configuration profile."""
 250
 251    def __init__(self, **kwargs):
 252        self.config = self.defaultConfig.copy()
 253
 254        # override defaults
 255        for key, value in kwargs.items():
 256            if key in self.config:
 257                self.config[key] = value
 258
 259        # call lambdas
 260        for key, value in self.config.items():
 261            if callable(value):
 262                self.config[key] = value(self.config)
 263
 264        # Create layers
 265        self.panel = cq.Workplane("XY")
 266        self.preview = cq.Workplane("XY")
 267        self.emboss = cq.Workplane("XY")
 268        self.supports = cq.Workplane("XY")
 269        self.drillTemplate = cq.Workplane("XY")
 270
 271        self.panelAdded = False  # We can only have one or horrible things happen

 283    def render(self, show_object=False):
 284        """You must call this before displaying or exporting your panel
 285        to post-process it properly.
 286
 287        If you give it the show_object function from Cq Editor as an
 288        argument, it will also display the object. When using Synth Printer
 289        from a different environment, just call without any argument.
 290        """
 291        # Shave off the sides of the panel if needed
 292        self.cutPanelWidthTolerance()
 293        # Move the supports where they belong
 294        self.supports = self.supports.translate(
 295            (0, 0, self.config["panelThickness"] / 2)
 296        )
 297        # Move the drill template above the panel
 298        self.drillTemplate = self.drillTemplate.translate(
 299            (0, 0, self.config["DrillTemplateDistance"])
 300        )
 301        # Rotate the layers for viewing
 302        self.panel = self.panel.rotate((0, 0, 0), (1, 0, 0), 180)
 303        self.preview = self.preview.rotate((0, 0, 0), (1, 0, 0), 180)
 304        self.emboss = self.emboss.rotate((0, 0, 0), (1, 0, 0), 180)
 305        self.supports = self.supports.rotate((0, 0, 0), (1, 0, 0), 180)
 306        self.drillTemplate = self.drillTemplate.rotate((0, 0, 0), (1, 0, 0), 180)
 307        # Display the layers if we're in CQ Editor
 308        if show_object and self.config["panelRender"]:
 309            show_object(
 310                self.panel,
 311                name="panel",
 312                options=self.config["panelShowOptions"],
 313            )
 314        if show_object and self.config["supportsRender"]:
 315            show_object(
 316                self.supports,
 317                name="supports",
 318                options=self.config["supportsShowOptions"],
 319            )
 320        if show_object and self.config["embossRender"]:
 321            show_object(
 322                self.emboss,
 323                name="emboss",
 324                options=self.config["embossShowOptions"],
 325            )
 326        if show_object and self.config["previewRender"]:
 327            show_object(
 328                self.preview,
 329                name="preview",
 330                options=self.config["previewShowOptions"],
 331            )
 332        if show_object and self.config["drillTemplateRender"]:
 333            show_object(
 334                self.drillTemplate,
 335                name="drillTemplate",
 336                options=self.config["drillTemplateShowOptions"],
 337            )

 376    def cutHole(self, x: float, y: float, diameter: float, depth: float = None):
 377        """Makes a circular hole, default depth is through the entire panel
 378
 379        x, y define the center."""
 380        self.panel = (
 381            self.panel.faces(">Z")
 382            .vertices("<XY")
 383            .workplane(centerOption="CenterOfMass")
 384            .center(x, y)
 385            .hole(diameter, depth)
 386        )
 387
 388    def cutRect(
 389        self,
 390        x: float,
 391        y: float,
 392        width: float,
 393        height: float,
 394        depth: float = 0,
 395        centered: bool = True,
 396    ):
 397        """Cuts a rectangular shape through the panel.
 398
 399        x, y define the center
 400
 401        `depth = 0` cuts through all.
 402        """
 403
 404        if depth == 0:
 405            depth = self.config["panelThickness"]
 406
 407        cutout = cq.Workplane("XY").box(width, height, depth)
 408
 409        if centered:
 410            cutout = cutout.translate(
 411                (
 412                    -self.config["panelWidth"] / 2 + x,
 413                    -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2 + y,
 414                    0,
 415                )
 416            )
 417        else:
 418            cutout = cutout.translate(
 419                (
 420                    -self.config["panelWidth"] / 2 + x + width / 2,
 421                    -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2 + y + height / 2,
 422                    0,
 423                )
 424            )
 425
 426        self.panel = (
 427            self.panel.faces(">Z")
 428            .vertices("<XY")
 429            .workplane(centerOption="CenterOfMass")
 430            .cut(cutout)
 431        )

 499    def addPanel(
 500        self,
 501        width: float,
 502        height: float,
 503        screwSlots: str = "auto",
 504    ):
 505        """Adds a rectangular panel of arbitrary dimensions.
 506        You can only add one.
 507
 508        Screw slots in the corners provide better tolerances than holes
 509        in a DIY printed system. If the panel is too small for four slots,
 510        there will be only two by default.
 511
 512
 513        TODO: Add Slots to the drill template
 514
 515
 516        screwSlots: options are "auto", "auto-tlbr", "auto-trbl", "auto-center", "none", "all", "tlbr", "trbl", "center"
 517        """
 518
 519        if self.panelAdded == True:
 520            raise Warning("Only one panel can be added")
 521        else:
 522            self.panelAdded = True
 523
 524        self.config["panelWidth"] = width
 525        self.config["panelHeight"] = height
 526
 527        # Make the main panel shape
 528        self.panel = self.panel.box(
 529            self.config["panelWidth"],
 530            self.config["panelHeight"],
 531            self.config["panelThickness"],
 532        )
 533
 534        # Initialize the drill template
 535        self.markOutline()
 536
 537        # Do we add screw slots?
 538        # default to "none" configuration
 539        screwSlotTopLeft = False
 540        screwSlotTopCenter = False
 541        screwSlotTopRight = False
 542        screwSlotBottomLeft = False
 543        screwSlotBottomCenter = False
 544        screwSlotBottomRight = False
 545        if (  # If too small for 4 slots
 546            self.config["m3screwSlotWidth"] * 2
 547            + (
 548                self.config["m3screwSlotDistanceFromSide"]
 549                - self.config["m3screwSlotWidth"] / 2
 550            )
 551            * 2
 552        ) > self.config["panelWidth"]:
 553            if screwSlots == "auto":
 554                screwSlots = "tlbr"
 555            if screwSlots == "auto-tlbr":
 556                screwSlots = "tlbr"
 557            if screwSlots == "auto-trbl":
 558                screwSlots = "trbl"
 559            if screwSlots == "auto-center":
 560                screwSlots = "center"
 561        else:  # Large enough for 4 slots
 562            if screwSlots == "auto":
 563                screwSlots = "all"
 564            if screwSlots == "auto-tlbr":
 565                screwSlots = "all"
 566            if screwSlots == "auto-trbl":
 567                screwSlots = "all"
 568            if screwSlots == "auto-center":
 569                screwSlots = "all"
 570        if screwSlots == "tlbr":
 571            screwSlotTopLeft = True
 572            screwSlotBottomRight = True
 573        if screwSlots == "trbl":
 574            screwSlotTopRight = True
 575            screwSlotBottomLeft = True
 576        if screwSlots == "center":
 577            screwSlotTopCenter = True
 578            screwSlotBottomCenter = True
 579        if screwSlots == "all":
 580            screwSlotTopLeft = True
 581            screwSlotTopRight = True
 582            screwSlotBottomLeft = True
 583            screwSlotBottomRight = True
 584
 585        screwPoints = []
 586        if screwSlotTopLeft:
 587            screwPoints.append(
 588                (
 589                    self.config["m3screwSlotDistanceFromSide"],
 590                    self.config["panelHeight"]
 591                    - self.config["m3screwSlotDistanceFromTop"],
 592                )
 593            )
 594        if screwSlotTopCenter:
 595            screwPoints.append(
 596                (
 597                    self.config["panelWidth"] / 2,
 598                    self.config["panelHeight"]
 599                    - self.config["m3screwSlotDistanceFromTop"],
 600                )
 601            )
 602        if screwSlotTopRight:
 603            screwPoints.append(
 604                (
 605                    self.config["panelWidth"]
 606                    - self.config["m3screwSlotDistanceFromSide"],
 607                    self.config["panelHeight"]
 608                    - self.config["m3screwSlotDistanceFromTop"],
 609                )
 610            )
 611        if screwSlotBottomLeft:
 612            screwPoints.append(
 613                (
 614                    self.config["m3screwSlotDistanceFromSide"],
 615                    self.config["m3screwSlotDistanceFromBottom"],
 616                )
 617            )
 618        if screwSlotBottomCenter:
 619            screwPoints.append(
 620                (
 621                    self.config["panelWidth"] / 2,
 622                    self.config["m3screwSlotDistanceFromBottom"],
 623                )
 624            )
 625        if screwSlotBottomRight:
 626            screwPoints.append(
 627                (
 628                    self.config["panelWidth"]
 629                    - self.config["m3screwSlotDistanceFromSide"],
 630                    self.config["m3screwSlotDistanceFromBottom"],
 631                )
 632            )
 633        if screwPoints != []:
 634            self.panel = (
 635                self.panel.faces(">Z")
 636                .workplane()
 637                .center(-self.config["panelWidth"] / 2, -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2)
 638                .pushPoints(screwPoints)
 639                .slot2D(
 640                    self.config["m3screwSlotWidth"],
 641                    self.config["m3screwSlotHeight"],
 642                    0,
 643                )
 644                .cutThruAll()
 645            )

 647    def addEurorackPanel(
 648        self,
 649        hp: int,
 650        screwSlots="auto",
 651    ):
 652        """Adds a Eurorack panel with screw slots. Eurorack width is defined in hp().
 653
 654        Eurorack sizes are generally an even number of hp, such as 4hp or 8hp.
 655        3hp and 5hp are the only odd number sizes commonly seen in commercial hardware.
 656
 657        Screw slots in the corners provide better tolerances than holes
 658        in a DIY printed system. If the panel is too small for four slots,
 659        there will be only two by default.
 660
 661        screwSlots: options are "auto", "auto-tlbr", "auto-trbl", "auto-center", "none", "all", "tlbr", "trbl", "center"
 662        """
 663        self.config["panelWidthTolerance"] = self.config["eurorackWidthTolerance"]
 664        self.addPanel(self.config["hp"] * hp, self.config["eurorackHeight"], screwSlots)
 665
 666    def add1UIJPanel(
 667        self,
 668        hp: int,
 669        screwSlots="auto",
 670    ):
 671        """Adds a 1U Tile (Intellijel size) panel with screw slots. Eurorack width is defined in hp().
 672
 673        Note that there are two incompatible 1U tile standards: Intellijel and PulpLogic.
 674
 675        Screw slots in the corners provide better tolerances than holes
 676        in a DIY printed system. If the panel is too small for four slots,
 677        there will be only two by default.
 678
 679        screwSlots: options are "auto", "auto-tlbr", "auto-trbl", "auto-center", "none", "all", "tlbr", "trbl", "center"
 680        """
 681        self.config["panelWidthTolerance"] = self.config["1UIJWidthTolerance"]
 682        self.addPanel(self.config["hp"] * hp, self.config["1UIJHeight"], screwSlots)
 683
 684    def addKosmoPanel(
 685        self,
 686        khp: int,
 687        screwSlots="auto",
 688    ):
 689        """Adds a Kosmo panel with screw slots. khp argument is the amount of 25mm columns.
 690
 691        Kosmo, also known as Metric 5U, is a format compatible with Eurorack
 692        popularized by Youtuber Sam Battle (Look Mum No Computer), that uses big jacks.
 693        It has a horizontal pitch of 25mm (called khp in Synth Printer for simplicity)
 694
 695        Screw slots in the corners provide better tolerances than holes
 696        in a DIY printed system. Kosmo panels are always large enough for four slots,
 697        but you can explicitly set a different configuration of slots.
 698
 699        screwSlots: options are "auto", "auto-tlbr", "auto-trbl", "auto-center", "none", "all", "tlbr", "trbl", "center"
 700        """
 701        self.config["panelWidthTolerance"] = self.config["kosmoWidthTolerance"]
 702        self.addPanel(
 703            self.config["khp"] * khp,
 704            self.config["kosmoHeight"],
 705            screwSlots=screwSlots,
 706        )

 708    def cutPanelWidthTolerance(self):
 709        """Automatically called during `render()` for Eurorack and 1UIJ:
 710        makes the panel a bit smaller than its nominal size laterally to account
 711        for thermal expansion and misaligned neighboring panels.
 712        Kosmo panels are naturally a bit smaller than the hp grid (they are on a
 713        25mm grid, while hp are on a 5.08mm grid), as a result, they don't need
 714        this shave.
 715        """
 716        # FIXME: Trial and error values that make no sense.
 717        # Something's broken elsewhere!
 718        # FIXME: Test print Euro / IJ: Do the tolerances provide enough extrusions?
 719        if self.config["panelWidthTolerance"] == 0:
 720            return
 721        self.cutRect(
 722            0,
 723            0,
 724            self.config["panelWidthTolerance"],
 725            self.config["panelHeight"] * 2,
 726            False,
 727        )
 728
 729        self.cutRect(
 730            self.config["panelWidth"] - self.config["panelWidthTolerance"] / 2,
 731            0,
 732            self.config["panelWidthTolerance"],
 733            self.config["panelHeight"] * 2,
 734            False,
 735        )

 741    def engraveLine(
 742        self,
 743        fromX: float,
 744        fromY: float,
 745        angle: float,
 746        length: float,
 747        width: float,
 748        depth: float = 0,
 749    ):
 750        """Engraves a line on the front of the panel.
 751
 752        If the depth parameter is omitted or 0, the default depth is used.
 753
 754        Be sure to inspect both sides of the print to make sure there aren't
 755        any sections that are too thin!
 756        """
 757        if not self.config["panelRender"]:
 758            return
 759        if depth == 0:
 760            depth = self.config["panelEngravingDepth"]
 761        cutout = (
 762            cq.Workplane("XY")
 763            .lineTo(-width / 2, 0)
 764            .lineTo(-width / 2, -length)
 765            .lineTo(width / 2, -length)
 766            .lineTo(width / 2, 0)
 767            .close()
 768            .extrude(depth)
 769            .rotate((0, 0, 0), (0, 0, 1), angle)
 770            .translate(
 771                (
 772                    -self.config["panelWidth"] / 2 + fromX,
 773                    -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2 + fromY,
 774                    -self.config["panelThickness"] / 2,
 775                )
 776            )
 777        )
 778        self.panel = (
 779            self.panel.faces(">Z")
 780            .vertices("<XY")
 781            .workplane(centerOption="CenterOfMass")
 782            .cut(cutout)
 783        )

 794    def cutRail(
 795        self,
 796        x: float,
 797        y: float,
 798        hpWidth: int,
 799        centered: bool = True,
 800        orientation: str = "horizontal",
 801    ):
 802        """Make a hole for a hp rail. The rail is added to the supports layer,
 803        not the panel layer."""
 804        if not self.config["panelRender"]:
 805            return
 806        width = hp(hpWidth) + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2
 807        height = self.config["railsHeight"] + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2
 808        if orientation == "vertical":
 809            width, height = height, width
 810        if centered:
 811            self.cutRect(x, y, width, height, 0, centered)
 812        else:
 813            self.cutRect(
 814                x - self.config["cradleTolerance"],
 815                y - self.config["cradleTolerance"],
 816                width,
 817                height,
 818                0,
 819                centered,
 820            )
 821
 822    def supportRail(
 823        self,
 824        _x: float,
 825        _y: float,
 826        hpWidth: int,
 827        centered: bool = True,
 828        orientation: str = "horizontal",
 829    ):
 830        """Adds a hp rail to the support layer. Requires a hole from cutRail()."""
 831        if not self.config["supportsRender"]:
 832            return
 833        width = hp(hpWidth) + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2
 834        height = self.config["railsHeight"] + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2
 835        if orientation != "horizontal":
 836            width, height = height, width
 837
 838        if centered:
 839            x = -self.config["panelWidth"] / 2 + _x
 840            y = -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2 + _y
 841        else:
 842            x = (
 843                -self.config["panelWidth"] / 2
 844                + _x
 845                + width / 2
 846                - self.config["cradleTolerance"]
 847            )
 848            y = (
 849                -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2
 850                + _y
 851                + height / 2
 852                - self.config["cradleTolerance"]
 853            )
 854
 855        self.supports = (
 856            # Extrude on the inside
 857            self.supports.moveTo(x, y)
 858            .rect(width, height)
 859            .extrude(-self.config["panelThickness"] + self.config["railsFrontRecess"])
 860            # Extrude on the back
 861            .moveTo(x, y)
 862            .rect(width, height)
 863            .extrude(self.config["railsSupportDepthBack"])
 864        )
 865
 866        if orientation == "horizontal":
 867            x = (
 868                -self.config["panelWidth"] / 2
 869                + _x
 870                + (self.config["hp"] - self.config["railsScrewDiameter"]) / 2
 871                + self.config["railsScrewDiameter"] / 2
 872            )
 873            if centered:
 874                x = x - hp(hpWidth) / 2
 875        else:
 876            y = (
 877                -self.config["panelHeight"] / 2
 878                + _y
 879                + (self.config["hp"] - self.config["railsScrewDiameter"]) / 2
 880                + self.config["railsScrewDiameter"] / 2
 881            )
 882            if centered:
 883                y = y - hp(hpWidth) / 2
 884
 885        # Can't get rarray to work here.
 886        if orientation == "horizontal":
 887            for n in range(hpWidth):
 888                self.supports = (
 889                    self.supports.moveTo(x + n * self.config["hp"], y)
 890                    .circle(self.config["railsScrewDiameter"] / 2)
 891                    .cutThruAll()
 892                )
 893        else:
 894            for n in range(hpWidth):
 895                self.supports = (
 896                    self.supports.moveTo(x, y + n * self.config["hp"])
 897                    .circle(self.config["railsScrewDiameter"] / 2)
 898                    .cutThruAll()
 899                )

 901    def addRail(
 902        self,
 903        x: float,
 904        y: float,
 905        hpWidth: int,
 906        centered: bool = True,
 907        orientation: str = "horizontal",
 908    ):
 909        """Adds a recessed hp rail. The rail is added to the supports layer,
 910         not the panel layer. Good to build cradles: put a Eurorack modules on
 911        a Kosmo faceplate, or 1U on a Eurorack one.
 912
 913        x, y define the center.
 914
 915        orientation is "horizontal" by default, otherwise "vertical"
 916        """
 917        self.cutRail(x, y, hpWidth, centered, orientation)
 918        self.supportRail(x, y, hpWidth, centered, orientation)

 961                    1.6,
 962                )
 963            else:
 964                self.previewBoxOnFront(
 965                    x + height / 2 + self.config["cradleTolerance"] * 2,

 968                    hp(hpWidth),
 969                    1.6,
